title: James O'Keefe will release 'hours' of newsroom footage
text: Conservative activist plans Wikileaks-style release of 'hundreds of hours' of footage of journalists at work in newsrooms - with CNN his main target O'Keefe spoke on Sean Hannity's show on Tuesday about an upcoming leak He said he had 'people on the inside' come to him with audio of newsrooms On Twitter he confirmed that the leaks will be coming from CNN's newsroom Project Veritas is best known for releasing videos that outed the DNC's alleged paid agitator network during the election The group has been accused in the past of editing said clips to misrepresent persons as having said things that they did not Published: 21:36 GMT, 22 February 2017 | Updated: 01:41 GMT, 23 February 2017 113 shares
